# Ant Design Styling Rule

When editing frontend UI, use Ant Design 5 theme tokens and component APIs instead of hard-coded values.

- Use Vietnamese with full diacritics for Vietnamese copy in docs and user-facing text.
- Keep UI aligned with `docs/agent-artifacts/02-design/ui-flow-spec.md`.
- Use Ant Design theme token overrides via `ConfigProvider` for brand customization.
- Use `theme.useToken()` hook or CSS variables when referencing tokens in custom styles.

Do not introduce hard-coded style literals for:
- Hex/RGBA colors (e.g. `#1B4F8A`, `rgba(...)`)
- Spacing numbers in `style` props outside of Ant Design's built-in spacing props
- Border radius values

Allowed patterns:

```tsx
// ✅ Good — use Ant Design components and theme tokens
import { theme } from 'antd';
const { token } = theme.useToken();
const cardStyle: React.CSSProperties = {
  background: token.colorBgContainer,
  borderRadius: token.borderRadius,
  padding: token.paddingLG,
};

// ✅ Good — use AntD Space/Flex for layout
<Space direction="vertical" size="large">...</Space>

// ❌ Bad — hard-coded
const cardStyle = { background: '#FFFFFF', borderRadius: 8, padding: 24 };
```

Stack reference: React 18 + Vite + TypeScript + Ant Design 5.
